{
  "stem": "3524.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I saw the barracks again today-- empty, washed, and with a clean wind blowing through them but still permeated by that awful smell of death.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I saw skeletons of men walking and creeping in a dazed way up and down the halls, unable yet to understand what-- that they were really being fed and nursed back to life.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Everything that medical skill could give them, they had received.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were first washed in sit-down bathtubs, and then clean and fresh clothes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They were put to bed in sunlit rooms with flowers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Whole blood was transfused into emaciated bodies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Nourishment was injected intravenously-- nourishment was injected intravenously when they could not digest strengthening soups, but more than anything else, the simple fact that humane care and decent surroundings had its effect.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In the first two days after the 120th moved in, only two men died.' [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well at first, I couldn't believe that they knew about that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they claimed innocence of that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I couldn't see how they could see the smoke from the chimneys and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] see the activity around the camp and not know, to some extent, how they could be ignorant of that fact.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I think there had developed at that time a 'I think I know what's going on, but I don't want to know' attitude that perhaps we sometimes are guilty of here in the United States as well.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We don't want to know and don't take the opportunity to find out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the commander, General Patton, [BACKROUND NOISE] had ordered that the quartermaster corps take trucks down and bring these people up there and show them the atrocities as we found them.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
